result.text:
Doesn’t look big. Keep it in sight and in front like a good defender. You don’t need a lot of force to redirect, but your target is the eyes. Gouge, poke, rake. Keep your footing, if you have it, prepare to submerge otherwise. 

A shark that size should be manageable. 

Unless it’s hungry.

Pensacola, Florida on Monday, July 3, 2023.

A large shark came very close to swimmers at Navarre Beach in the Florida Panhandle. (No Attack)

The sighting was caught on camera, and people could be heard yelling to others to get out of the water.

Experts say shark sightings are more common in June than any other month because they like to come close to the shore to hunt, so it’s no surprise to see them still around in early July.
